<i>noun</i>: 훈화 [훈ː화], 훈시 [훈ː시], 통첩 [통첩], 지시 [지시], 지도 [지도], 시달 [시ː달], 명령문 [명ː녕문], 교습 [교ː습], 교수 [교ː수] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훈화 [훈ː화]</dt><br>
<dd>instruction; preaching; admonition</dd><br>
<dd>교훈이나 가르침을 주는 말을 함. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving another a talk that contains instructive contents or moral lessons; or such a talk.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훈시 [훈ː시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. instruction; direction; order</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람에게 맡은 일을 처리할 때에 주의할 점을 일러 줌.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving an order or request to one's subordinate regarding matters that require attention when handling one's own mission.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lesson; preaching; teaching</dd><br>
<dd>가르치거나 타이름.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of teaching or persuading another.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>통첩 [통첩]</dt><br>
<dd>notification; notice; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사실을 문서로 알림. 또는 그 문서.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of informing someone of a certain fact in a document; or such a document.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>지시 [지시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. indication; gesture</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 것을 가리켜서 보게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of pointing at something to make others look at it.</dd><br>
<dd>2. order; command; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>무엇을 하라고 시킴. 또는 그 내용.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of giving a command, or such a command.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>지도 [지도]</dt><br>
<dd>1. guidance; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 목적이나 방향으로 다른 사람을 가르쳐 이끎.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of teaching and leading another person towards a certain purpose or direction.</dd><br>
<dd>2. guidance; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>선생님이 학생에게 공부나 바른 생활을 가르침.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of a teacher giving instructions to a student regarding studies or the right way of living.</dd><br>
<dd>3. warning</dd><br>
<dd>유도에서 금지된 기술 및 동작을 할 때 받는 주의.</dd><br>
<dd>An alert given in judo when one performs a banned technique or action.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>시달 [시ː달]</dt><br>
<dd>1. order</dd><br>
<dd>높은 직위나 기관에서 그보다 낮은 직위나 기관으로 명령이나 문서를 전달함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of delivering an order or document issued by a high position or institution to a lower position or institution.</dd><br>
<dd>2. instruction</dd><br>
<dd>국가의 사무를 담당하는 기관에서 국민에게 알릴 내용을 문서로 전달함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of delivering a document issued by an institution in charge of national affairs to the people in order to inform them of something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>명령문 [명ː녕문]</dt><br>
<dd>1. command; instruction; directive</dd><br>
<dd>무엇을 시키거나 행동을 요구하는 명령의 내용을 적은 글.</dd><br>
<dd>A statement or written message that orders something or requests for a certain action.</dd><br>
<dd>2. imperative sentence</dd><br>
<dd>화자가 청자에게 무엇을 시키거나 행동을 요구하는 문장.</dd><br>
<dd>A sentence in which the speaker commands the addressee to do something or take a certain action.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>교습 [교ː습]</dt><br>
<dd>training; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>지식이나 기술 등을 가르쳐 익히게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of teaching and enabling one to learn knowledge or techniques, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>교수 [교ː수]</dt><br>
<dd>1. teaching; instruction</dd><br>
<dd>학생을 가르침.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of teaching students.</dd><br>
<dd>2. professor</dd><br>
<dd>대학에서 학문을 연구하고 가르치는 일을 하는 사람. 또는 그 직위.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who researches and teaches in colleges; or such a position.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>